honeywell.printer

Class DocumentExPCL_LP

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.Document
      • honeywell.printer.DocumentExPCL_LP

  • public class DocumentExPCL_LP
extends Document
    This class is use to build a print job for ExPCL language, Line Print mode. These functions can be used to 'build' a document using abstract methods instead of the raw 'ExPCL Line Print' mode commands. The DocumentExPCL_LP class is designed when users want to print in line print mode with an ExPCL language printer (Apex Series).

      • writeBarCodePDF417

        public void writeBarCodePDF417(java.lang.String textString,
                               int redundancyLevel)
        This function will print the provided text to the document as a PDF417 2D barcode using the provided printing parameter values.
        Parameters:
        textString - Text to print as PDF417 2D barcode.
        redundancyLevel - This will set the number of redundant code words used to protect against data loss/corruption. The typical value is 1 which would result in 4 code words. Other values are 2 giving you 8 code words, 3 giving you 16 code words up to 8 giving you 512 code words.

      • writeImage

        public void writeImage(java.lang.String imagePath,
                       int printHeadWidth)
        This will cause the image specified to be printed. Images will be expanded to occupy the entire width of the printer, so the correct current width of the printer must be specified. Images that are too wide will be cropped, and images that are too narrow will be padded on the right.
        Parameters:
        imagePath - Image file path of the PNG or BMP image to be printed.
        printHeadWidth - Width of the print head in dots. Usually 384 for 2 inch printers, 576 for 3 inch and 832 for 4 inch.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - Exception has occurred

      • writeImage

        This will cause the image specified to be printed. Images will be expanded to occupy the entire width of the printer, so the correct current width of the printer must be specified. Images that are too wide will be cropped, and images that are too narrow will be padded on the right.

      • writeImage

        public void writeImage(android.graphics.Bitmap imageObject,
                       int printHeadWidth,
                       int darknessThreshold)
                throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        This will cause the image specified to be printed. Images will be expanded to occupy the entire width of the printer, so the correct current width of the printer must be specified. Images that are too wide will be cropped, and images that are too narrow will be padded on the right.
        Parameters:
        imageObject - Image to print
        printHeadWidth - Width of the print head in dots. Usually 384 for 2 inch printers, 576 for 3 inch and 832 for 4 inch.
        darknessThreshold - Threshold to adjust darkness of the image. Valid values are 0 - 255.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if any of the parameter values are not in the valid range this exception is thrown.
        Since:
        1.1.0

      • advanceToNextPage

        public void advanceToNextPage()
        This command will causes a form feed to occur from the papers current location. The size of a form can be set with the setPageLength() function.

      • advanceToQueueMark

        public void advanceToQueueMark(byte additionalRows)
        This will advance the paper to the next queue mark and an additional number of dotlines as specified by the input parameter.
        Parameters:
        additionalRows - Number of dotlines to move beyond the queue mark. Each dotline is 1/8mm high and valid values are between 0 and 65535.
